{
    "name": "Squire",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Tactics",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>During Combat </b>If serving a knight, the aristocrat fights near his master, making frequent use of flanking and aid another. He stays mounted to take advantage of his horse\u2019s attacks."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "html": "This squire has begun his knightly training, but not yet earned his spurs. He aspires to match the valor and chivalry of the finest knights. Most of his duties involve caring for his knight\u2019s armor, weapons, and horse, holding prisoners taken by the knight, and giving the knight an honorable burial if he is killed.<br/><br/>The knight may instruct the squire to follow him into battle. If the squire proves himself loyal, skilled, and reliable in combat, his knight may choose to elevate him to full knight status (though in some lands this ceremony may only be performed by the ruler). A knight may have many squires, but a squire serves only one knight."
        }
    ],
